{
  "stem": "14387.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She skied right across with a child in her back-- Adella.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sweden was very peaceful, but it was like sitting on a keg of dynamite.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You didn't know, from one day to another, if the Germans could invade.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You see, Sweden allowed German troops to travel across.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's well-known.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In order to get their troops across, to-- the fastest way would be to travel across Sweden.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Sweden consented to this.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Not because they wanted to-- well, I'm not going to go into politics, of course-- not because they wanted to, but because if they hadn't, Germany would have just gone in and taken the whole country.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So they allowed the German troops to travel across into Norway.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the thought was, if Germany kept on demanding things of Sweden, Sweden would do it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so, what would happen?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't know-- we didn't know where we were from day to day.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So, as I say, my husband was a very adventurous person.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He said, I want to go to the United States.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He didn't ever thought to live in the United States for the rest of his life, just until the war's over.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so, that's what we did.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We applied to the United States for a visa.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At first, they refused-- they didn't grant us a visa, but then later on, they wrote to us and said they would-- It was a little politics.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was before the elections, and they weren't making any changes or something, so, anyway, they did grant us visas.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, remember, we only lived in Sweden for one-- I'm talking about 50 years ago.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everything's not so clear in my mind.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
